<p>It’s hard to even write about this one because my feelings on it are so complex. I loved and hated it
at the same time. I’m so glad it exists. I wish there had been less detail on the lives of people
she wrote about who couldn’t consent to their stories being told in public. It feels like one important
part of the start to a shift in how we talk about race and Asian-American experiences, as Asian Americans.</p>
